Sarah Thomas is a referee for college football's Conference USA . 
  She is the first woman to be hired as a full-time NFL referee for the 2015 season . 
  The 42-year-old mother of three has been part of the NFL training program since 2013 . 
  She became the first female to officiate a college football game in 2007 and the first to preside over a bowl game in 2009 . 
  Thomas will be among eight new hires for the NFL for 2015 . 
  Shannon Eastin was the first women to referee an NFL game in 2012 . 
  The NFL is the second major league to hire a female referee after the NBA hired Violet Palmer and Dee Kantner in 1997 . 
 